(a)  Any corporation desiring to be licensed as an escrow depository shall file an application upon forms to be furnished by the commissioner.  The application shall be accompanied by a filing fee no part of which shall be refundable.
	(b)  The application shall contain the following information:



	(1)	The corporate name, amount of capital, and office address of the applicant;
	(2)	The names of the stockholders, officers, and directors of the applicant;
	(3)	Evidence of the character, financial responsibility, experience, and ability of the officers and directors; and
	(4)	The names of the proposed escrow officers and their qualifications. [L 1967, c 144, pt of §1; HRS ; am L 1985, c 269, §50; am L 1992, c 205, §6]
